# .cursorrules
# CRM Lead Management — NestJS Backend
# Auto-loaded by Cursor/Windsurf every session. Always active.

## READ FIRST EVERY SESSION
1. docs/07_OPERATIONS_LOG.md  — Current project state & session history
2. docs/01_PROJECT_META.md    — Tech stack, setup, and scope audit
3. docs/02_ARCHITECTURE_STANDARDS.md — Non-negotiable laws

## AI AGENT LOGGING (MANDATORY)
Every session must log its intent and outcome:
- **START**: Use a `<thought>` block to analyze the "last 3 entries" in `07_OPERATIONS_LOG.md` for context alignment. Log "Intent" to `ai_operation_logs` (status: pending).
- **END**: Update log with "Outcome" (success/fail) via `fn_log_ai_operation` and update `07_OPERATIONS_LOG.md`.

## ARCHITECTURE — NEVER BREAK
- ALL business logic in PostgreSQL dispatcher functions only (docs/03_DATABASE_CORE.md)
- NestJS service methods: return this.db.callDispatcher(fn, payload) ONLY
- NestJS controllers: validate DTO + call service + return result ONLY
- Cookie: crm_session HttpOnly — NO JWT — NO Bearer tokens
- Soft deletes: deleted_at = NOW() — NEVER DELETE FROM — Check for dependencies (Role/User) first.
- Concurrency: Use `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE` in SQL for critical mutations to prevent race conditions.
- Storage: Use `StorageProvider` interface in `DocumentService` — No raw `fs` in logic.
- Response Envelope: { rid, statusCode, data, message, errors, meta }

## SQL INJECTION PREVENTION (docs/03_DATABASE_CORE.md)
- NEVER EXECUTE with string concat -> ALWAYS format() with %I or %L
- NEVER ILIKE without fn_escape_like() + ESCAPE '\'
- ALWAYS cast JSONB to types: (p_data->>'id')::UUID, (p_data->>'status')::lead_status
- ALWAYS SET search_path = public on SECURITY DEFINER functions

## NESTJS RULES (docs/04_API_AUTH_AND_UI_CONFIG.md)
- class-validator DTOs — whitelist:true, transform:true
- @UseGuards(SessionGuard) on all. @Roles('admin') on admin routes.
- Use docs/04_API_AUTH_AND_UI_CONFIG.md for Error rid registry (e.g. e-lead-not-found)

## BUILD ORDER
Auth -> Users -> Contacts -> Leads -> Projects -> Tasks -> Documents -> 
Communications -> Quotations -> Expenses -> Workflows -> Notifications -> 
Dashboard -> Reports -> Search -> Audit -> Integrations -> Project Shares

